core:processNote.core:description: Complete float transaction now so we can print a receipt immediately (even though we might void the cashup)

core:assignAction.core:comment: Set a simple flag that the prompts can use to determine which button captions to use.
Saves the closing float transaction handler etc. in the process so that the shared transaction handler can be re-used for the cash up transaction.

core:endProcessAction.core:comment: The Fail outcome indicates that the current basket need not be discarded.

core:action.core:comment: Dummy action to ensure that all privileges used in sub-processes and CheckPrivilegesAction are also listed against this process in the role maintenance app.

core:assignAction.core:comment: Because SetSessionDetails is executed remotely we must save the updated COPY of the transaction in our handler.
If the transaction is updated by a web service this action will output a new transaction entity which must replace the original transaction referenced by the transaction handler.

core:executeProcessAction.core:name: Terminal Cashup and Leave
core:executeProcessAction.core:comment: Finalise the same terminal and automatically accept the cashup values.
